2026-06-17  Bug fix (item 13 regression): every undo/redo crashed the performer LiveView — the "select-task" push sent task_id as an integer, the client re-emitted it to select_task, and String.to_integer/1 crashed on the integer, re-mounting the page and masking the (already-succeeded) reversal. Push the id as a string; hardened the item-13 test to round-trip select_task so it can not recur.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 +item 14 (draft): make completion (done ⇄ open) undoable — record status_changed + its inverse incl. the Arc-3 cascade-complete (deferred in item 2), closing the "every mutation reversible" goal. Core undo work, not O&C (that is out-of-arc gaps). O&C renumbered to item 15, Testing gate to item 16.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14 (draft) scope expanded after the Cheese "Nothing to undo" repro: completing a leaf records no status event and fragments into per-ancestor progress_changed up to the root (done=>manual_progress coupling + cascade), so an out-of-domain root event walls a viewer+ off from undoing their own in-subtree completion. Item 14 now records one atomic completion event on the acted task (covers the up/down cascade, no fragmentation). The 16.2 testing item notes the surfaced failure (re-verified at 16.9) instead of burying it under the passing cutoff check.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14 implemented: completion (done <-> open) is undoable. toggle_complete/cascade_status now record ONE atomic status_changed event on the task the user toggled, its inverse_payload capturing every task the flip touched (acted task + cascaded ancestors + cascaded descendants) with prior/next status+manual_progress; the per-task progress_changed spam is suppressed (update_task record_events?: false). undo/redo restore the whole cascade in one step and reconcile roll-ups; rights-gated on the acted task so a viewer+ can undo a completion in their led subtree (fixes the Cheese "Nothing to undo" where an out-of-domain root event walled them off). Reversal broadcasts a structural reload since roll-ups ripple to ancestors. 250 tests green.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14 reversal broadcast: now one {:task_updated} per affected task (mirrors the forward path) instead of one structural reload -- patch_task covers the acted task lineage (leaf + up-cascade), and a branch down-cascade descendants each get their own. Cost proportional to the change; the prior always-reload was correct but heavier and inconsistent with the forward path.
