2026-06-20  Bug fix (UX_GUARDRAILS §6.5): the move-flip confirm now fires client-side. A reorganizing drag that would silently flip an ancestor's completion predicts the flip from the DOM at drop time and opens the confirm instantly (no round trip), holding the optimistic placement until the user decides (Proceed re-sends move_task confirmed:true; Cancel reverts). The server's #completion-confirm stays the authoritative backstop for any flip the client doesn't predict.
2026-06-20  Tweak: a permission denial now sounds the rejection bonk. Every "You don't have permission" path in the Initiative view (add/edit/move/assign/progress/toggle/...) pushes a "bonk" event the TaskKeys hook plays, so a viewer / viewer+ attempting a disallowed action gets the audible thud however the attempt arrived (key, form, click, drop) — not just the flash.
2026-06-20  Fix: Leave Initiative no longer round-trips before its confirm (no-round-trip-before-input / UX_GUARDRAILS 6.5). The confirm now opens client-side (#leave-confirm, like the delete confirms) with its own correct "Leave Initiative" heading — it had been borrowing the generic completion modal, which read "Confirm completion change." Only Proceed touches the server (leave_initiative now commits directly); the dead pending/confirm_pending leave path is gone.
2026-06-20  Follow-up: leaving an Initiative now shows a "Leaving…" in-flight state instead of dismissing the confirm. Leaving is server-confirmed (you're navigated away only when the members_changed broadcast ejects the view), so Proceed holds the modal in a pulsing disabled "Leaving…" state until commit — no dead-air return to a live-looking initiative. leave_initiative replies ok:true/false; a refusal or dropped reply (8s) restores the confirm; backdrop/Cancel/Esc are inert mid-commit.
2026-06-20  Fix (chat, item 3.1): the collapse chevron was inverted — it pointed down when collapsed. The chat docks at the bottom and opens upward, so it now points up when collapsed ("open") and down when open ("minimize").
2026-06-20  Chat (item 3.1 follow-up): when a message arrives while the chat is collapsed, the title bar peeks the latest message (dimmed italic, single-line ellipsis) between "Chat" and the chevron; opening the chat clears the peek.
2026-06-20  Chat (item 3.1 follow-up): an incoming message from another viewer now plays a short rising "pop" (distinct from the descending rejection bonk); if the chat is collapsed it also flashes green. Both suppressed for your own messages (matched on the message's user_id vs yours).
2026-06-20  Nav: notifications now own a dedicated bell (hero-bell) + dropdown carrying the unread red dot, shown at every breakpoint (mobile too, NOT in the hamburger); opening still marks read and the flyout list/links are reused as-is. Removed the duplicated notifications flyout from the user menu and hamburger. Account, bell, and hamburger menus now use the KeepOpen hook so a live re-render (e.g. an incoming notification over PubSub) no longer snaps an open dropdown shut.
2026-06-20  Fix (confirm sweep): Archive no longer round-trips before its confirm (UX_GUARDRAILS 6.5). The confirm opens client-side (#archive-confirm) — the owner case predicts "any incomplete task" from the DOM; the member case is caught by a server backstop (reply needs_confirm, only when there's unfinished work). archive_initiative commits on confirmed:true or a clean tree; the old assign_pending :archive path + its modal copy are gone. (Hide already had no confirm — clean.)
2026-06-20  Fix (intermediate width): the Show/Hide Members toggle now shows below lg (was phone-only), so at the sm–lg width you can open Members without selecting a task (the pinned panel is lg:+ and the Details flyout only brings Members when a task is open). New List in that block stays phone-only (the title-row New List covers sm:+).
2026-06-20  Nav: the notifications bell now sits immediately left of the avatar at every breakpoint (pulled the account menu out of the links wrapper; grouped links / bell / account(sm:+) / hamburger(<sm)). Was anchored far-left, reading wrong once the desktop nav appeared.
2026-06-20  Fix (chat): the chat window no longer closes after you send. The panel div is server-rendered with `hidden`, so a re-render (your own message broadcasting back) had morphdom re-apply it and snap the open chat shut; the .Chat hook now re-asserts the open state from localStorage in updated().
2026-06-20  Fix (confirm sweep): Remove member no longer round-trips before its confirm. The "Remove X?" intent confirm opens client-side (#remove-member-confirm, name client-known, UX_GUARDRAILS 6.5); only Proceed pushes remove_member, which commits or — for a member holding assignments — escalates to the server hand-off modal (whose content is server data, so that round trip is legitimate). Dropped the assign_pending :remove_member path + its modal copy and the per-action "don't ask again" suppression for this confirm (it's instant now).
2026-06-20  Tweak: keep the New List and Show/Hide Members buttons together below lg. The intermediate-width fix had left Members alone (New List came from the title row); now New List rides in that same row at all <lg widths and the title-row New List takes over only at lg:+.
2026-06-20  Tweak (chat): the chat now defaults CLOSED on every load (in-memory open state, no longer persisted to localStorage) — it no longer greets you open after a refresh / initiative open.
2026-06-20  Fix (archive confirm regression, UX_GUARDRAILS 6.5): the owner's archive confirm round-tripped instead of opening client-side. The app.js click handler looked for an incomplete row via [data-done="false"], but data-done is a boolean attr HEEx omits when false — incomplete rows carry NO data-done at all, so the selector matched nothing and every owner fell through to the server backstop. Selector now :not([data-done]); an owner with any incomplete task gets the instant #archive-confirm, an all-done Initiative still archives immediately.
2026-06-20  Chat (item 3.1): sending with nobody else viewing now bonks and drops a dimmed system line into your own log ("Nobody's here to read that yet — no one else is viewing this Initiative.") instead of silently broadcasting into the void. "No other viewer" = @online_ids (per-Initiative presence) minus you is empty; the alone case skips the broadcast (no reader) and appends a local-only system message. System lines carry no avatar/user_id and are marked data-chat-system so the .Chat hook never pops/flashes/previews them.
